\par\par \b \uc2 New car financing surges despite lower automobile sales in first quarter 2024\b0\par\par\uc2 Aditya Hadi , The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \uc2 493 \uc2 words\par \uc2 15 May 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 5\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2024 The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2 Multifinance firms saw outstanding loans for new cars continue to increase in the first quarter of this year despite carmakers reporting a drop in sales.\par \par \uc2 The Financial Services Authority (OJK) stated on Monday that outstanding loans for new car purchases rose by 14.19 percent year-on-year (yoy) in the first three months of this year.\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, carmakers saw new car sales down by 23.9 percent yoy to 215,000 units in the same period, according to Association of Indonesian Automotive Manufacturers (Gaikindo) data.\par \par \uc2 "The OJK will continue to monitor the impact of the drop in new vehicle sales on the performance of multifinance firms," said Agusman, the OJK's supervisor for multifinance, venture capital and other financial services, during a press briefing.\par \par \uc2 Overall, outstanding loans of multifinance firms grew 12.17 percent to Rp 488.52 trillion (US$30.36 billion) in March, much higher than the 11.73 percent yoy recorded the preceding month.\par \par \uc2 On May 6, major credit rating agency \uc2 Fitch Ratings\uc2  said the decline in new car sales in Indonesia may push local multifinance companies to seek growth in other sectors, such as used car loans.\par \par \uc2 Fitch\uc2  suggested that new car purchases were unlikely to accelerate significantly for the rest of the year, as the benchmark interest rate hike by \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  in April could lead to higher car-financing rates.\par \par \uc2 The firm now expects new car sales to fall to around 900,000 vehicles in 2024, compared with its earlier expectation that the figure would remain close to the 1 million units sold in 2023.\par \par \uc2 "We still expect the financing and leasing sector receivables to expand at a high single-digit rate this year, though this outlook could be threatened if auto sales fall by more than we assume," \uc2 Fitch\uc2  said in a statement.\par \par \uc2 Indonesian banks saw a 12.4 percent hike in loan disbursement to Rp 7.25 quadrillion as of March, marking much stronger growth than the 11.28 percent recorded in February.\par \par \uc2 Most of this growth was driven by state-owned banks, which saw their loan disbursement surge 13.72 percent during the period. Investment credit was the type of loan that recorded the fastest growth in the first quarter.\par \par \uc2 Amid the surging loan disbursement, lenders were also able to improve their nonperforming loans (NPLs) to 2.25 percent in March from previously 2.35 percent in the preceding month.\par \par \uc2 The OJK expressed optimism that local banking credit would still grow by more than 10 percent this year, despite the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 The agency also explained that the volatility of the rupiah did not have a significant impact on banks' capital liquidity, based on stress tests it conducted.\par \par \uc2 The OJK cited the net foreign exchange position (PDN) of local banks remained at 1.66 percent, far below the threshold of 20 percent.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020240514ek5f0000c\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
