\par\par \b \uc2 Minister Sri Mulyani Monitors Indonesia's  \highlight22\uc2 Economy \highlight\uc2  Post-Iranian President Death\b0\par\par\uc2 355 \uc2 words\par \uc2 22 May 2024\par \uc2 Tempo.co\par \uc2 TEMPOE\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. PT Tempo Inti Media, Tbk \par \par \uc2 TEMPO.CO, Jakarta - Minister of Finance Sri Mulyani monitors the impact of the death of Iranian President \uc2 Ebrahim Raisi\uc2  on Indonesia\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . According to her, the world\u8217\'20\'19s dynamics are moving rapidly. "We'll see what the results are," said Sri Mulyani when met at the Presidential Palace in Jakarta on Wednesday, May 22, 2024.\par \par \uc2 Sri Mulyani was reluctant to elaborate further on her statement. When asked about the exchange rate of the rupiah which nearly touched Rp16,000 against the US dollar, the former Managing Director of the \uc2 World Bank\uc2  said she would discuss macroeconomic \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the focal points of \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  with the parliament. "The meeting will become a formal forum to discuss the issue from various points of view," she said.\par \par \uc2 The rupiah closed at Rp15,999 against the US dollar yesterday and opened stronger at Rp15,980 this morning.\par \par \uc2 Analysts are observing the oil markets to see how they react to further \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the Middle East following Raisi's death. The president\u8217\'20\'19s passing worried the financial markets, especially commodities, as Iran's position in the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  became an increasingly unstable post-drone attack on Israel last month.\par \par \uc2 Iran is the world\u8217\'20\'19s largest oil producer and further conflict involving the country threatens the stability of the Middle East, especially as it\u8217\'20\'19s seen as supporting the Yemen-based Houthi in blocking international shipping from crossing the Red Sea.\par \par \uc2 President \uc2 Joko Widodo\uc2  previously hoped that the death of Iranian President \uc2 Ebrahim Raisi\uc2  would not affect the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , especially oil prices.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CBecause once oil prices rise due to the incident, it will spill over on other things, including prices of goods. We hope to avoid such impacts,\u8221\'20\'1D said Jokowi during his visit to Batu Taba shelter, Agam Regency, West Sumatra, on Tuesday, May 21, 2024, quoted from a video statement.\par \par \uc2 DANIEL A. FAJRI\par \par \uc2 Editor\u8217\'20\'19s Choice: Statistics Indonesia: Iran-Israel Conflict Bears No Significant Impact on Indonesian Trade\par \par \uc2 Click here to get the latest news updates from Tempo on Google News\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://statik.tempo.co/data/2024/05/22/id_1304134/1304134_720.jpg"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Click here to view picture}}}\par \par \uc2 Document TEMPOE0020240522ek5m000b5\par }\page {\par\fs20\uc2 Business\par \b \uc2 BI Keeps Rates Unchanged, Prioritizing Stability Amidst Global  \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainties \highlight\b0\par\par\uc2 494 \uc2 words\par \uc2 22 May 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Globe\par \uc2 JGLOBE\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. PT Jakarta Globe Media. \par \par \uc2 Jakarta. \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI)\uc2  decided to maintain the benchmark interest rate (BI rate) at 6.25 percent. Meanwhile, the deposit facility rate is kept at 5.5 percent and the lending facility rate is 7 percent.\par \par \uc2 "This decision is consistent with the pro-stability monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as a preemptive and forward-looking step to ensure that inflation remains within the target of 2.5\u177\'00\'B11 percent in 2024 and 2025. This includes maintaining the effectiveness of managing the inflow of foreign capital and the stability of the rupiah exchange rate," said BI Governor \uc2 Perry Warjiyo\uc2  in a press conference following the Monthly Board of Governors Meeting on Wednesday.\par \par \uc2 He said that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  continues to implement macro-prudential policies and a pro-growth payment system to support sustainable \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth. Loose macro-prudential policies are being pursued to encourage bank credit/financing to businesses and households.\par \par \uc2 "Infrastructure and the structure of the payment system industry, as well as expanding digital payment access," said Perry.\par \par \uc2 Furthermore, he stated that to maintain macroeconomic stability and support sustainable \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth amidst high \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the global financial markets, BI is strengthening the mix of monetary, macro-prudential, and payment system policies.\par \par \uc2 BI is enhancing \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  coordination with the central government, local governments, and strategic partners, including the National Movement for Controlling Food Inflation (GNPIP) programs in various regions under the Central and Regional Inflation Control Teams (TPIP and TPID), as well as the Acceleration and Expansion of Central and Regional Government Transaction Digitalization (P2DD).\par \par \uc2 "BI will continue to strengthen pro-stability monetary policies and enhance synergy with the central and regional governments so that inflation in 2024 and 2024 remains controlled within the range of 2.5\u177\'00\'B11 percent," explained Perry.\par \par \uc2 Previously, macroeconomic and financial market economist at the University of Indonesia Teuku Riefky predicted that BI would maintain the benchmark interest rate at 6.25 percent. This is because Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is in a better condition after facing significant pressure on prices and exchange rates for several months.\par \par \uc2 "After BI decided to raise the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  interest rate last month, there seems to be no urgency to change the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  interest rate in the Board of Governors Meeting," explained Riefky.\par \par \uc2 He emphasized that with the end of El Nino and the active role of the government in stabilizing food supplies through imports successfully lowering food prices and overall inflation levels. The inflation pressure from food prices has subsided during the 2024 Eid al-Fitr period compared to the last three years.\par \par \uc2 This will be a positive catalyst to maintain overall inflation in line with BI's target of 1.5%-3.5%. However, the potential risk of inflation is still visible and must be mitigated properly.\par \par \uc2 "Prolonged external pressure has weakened the rupiah in recent weeks. If this trend continues, it could have a negative impact on domestic price levels through import inflation," concluded Riefky.\par \par \uc2 Document JGLOBE0020240522ek5m00002\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
