\par\par \b \uc2 Analysis: Unlocking potential of nature-based solutions in Indonesia\b0\par\par\uc2 954 \uc2 words\par \uc2 12 June 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 4\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2024 The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2 Andjarsari Paramaditha, Mandiri, Jakarta\par \par \uc2 Nature-based solutions (NbS) is not a new concept, but its adoption in Indonesia is still limited.\par \par \uc2 Given the country's rich biodiversity, extensive coastlines and significant forest cover, it is well-positioned to implement NbS effectively. However, the challenges of adopting nature-based solutions are quite extensive and includes impact measuring, funding and investment as well as regulatory barriers.\par \par \uc2 Still, it has the potential to become one of the key environmental, social and governance (ESG) investments that Indonesia can offer to international markets in the future.\par \par \uc2 In recent years, nature and biodiversity have gained traction in the investment sphere as environmental and sustainability factors become rising concerns in current business practices.\par \par \uc2 Climate and nature are inextricably intertwined, as are biodiversity and climate change. According to estimates from the \uc2 World \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Forum\uc2 , nature contributes more than half of global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  production. Preserving and restoring nature is deemed necessary to reduce climate hazards, as well as to benefit from as part of the green \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  of the future.\par \par \uc2 Sustainable standards are among the trends companies today are required to adopt, not only for compliance or risk management but also as an opportunity to rethink their business models. This will be beneficial for various ESG investment instruments, including NbS.\par \par \uc2 Nature-based solutions, according to the \uc2 International Union for Conservation of Nature and Natural Resources\uc2 , address societal challenges through actions to protect, sustainably manage and restore nature and modify ecosystems, which will benefit both people and the environment. NbS target major challenges like climate change, disaster risk reduction, food and water security, biodiversity loss, human health and other factors that are critical to sustainable development.\par \par \uc2 Some NbS initiatives include mangrove, peatland and coral reef restoration. Projects such as sustainable agriculture, forest conservation and reforestation, urban forestry and integrated watershed management can also be considered NbS.\par \par \uc2 While it refers to sustainable environmental \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activities, NbS projects span a vast range of initiatives by leveraging natural processes. There are diverse applications of NbS from urban settings to rural landscapes. Each of these projects highlights potential to address numerous environmental and socioeconomic challenges.\par \par \uc2 Mangrove restoration provides coastal protection, reduces erosion, supports biodiversity and local fishery-related livelihoods and creates a carbon sink. Peatlands accumulate large amounts of carbon and play a critical role in water \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2 , especially in mitigating fires and haze.\par \par \uc2 Coral reefs support marine biodiversity, protect coastlines and sustain tourism and fisheries, but are vulnerable to climate change and human activities.\par \par \uc2 Sustainable agriculture promotes biodiversity, improves soil health, reduces greenhouse gas emissions, supports food security and improves farmers' resilience to climate change.\par \par \uc2 Forest conservation and reforestation are fundamental for carbon capture, biodiversity conservation, maintaining the water cycle and preventing soil erosion. Urban forestry develops green spaces, improves air quality, enhances urban biodiversity and integrates green infrastructure like green roofs and vertical gardens into urban planning.\par \par \uc2 Integrated watershed management creates a sustainable water supply, reduces flood risks and balances land use activities with water conservation.\par \par \uc2 These NbS projects engage local communities, which can then also be considered to have a social impact. Activities such as planting and maintaining mangroves, encouraging organic farming practices, conserving reefs and developing sustainable marine tourism ensure sustainability. They can also have socioeconomic benefits, such as creating jobs, supporting ecotourism and enhancing marine and agricultural productivity.\par \par \uc2 In Indonesia, nature-based solutions that incorporate natural processes and ecosystems to address climate change, disaster risk and sustainable development challenges are still limited but available. Since 2015, the Peat Restoration Agency (BRG) has been in charge of restoring 2 million hectares of degraded peatlands in seven priority provinces: Jambi, Riau, South Sumatra, Central Kalimantan, South Kalimantan, West Kalimantan and Papua.\par \par \uc2 With over 20 percent of the world's mangrove inhabited (around 3.2 million ha), there is also the Indonesia Blue Forests Project, which targets mangrove and seagrass habitat restoration. Part of the project is located in Tomini Bay, North Sulawesi, and in the Derawan Islands of East Kalimantan.\par \par \uc2 Additionally, the \uc2 World Bank\uc2  has been funding the Mangroves for Coastal Resilience initiative since 2022. This project aims to restore 600,000 ha of mangroves by 2024, said to be the largest mangrove restoration objective in the world to date.\par \par \uc2 However, there are still several challenges ahead regarding the implementation of NbS in Indonesia. Integrated regulatory policies from both local and national governments are not yet in place.\par \par \uc2 Government policies that support these projects are crucial, moreover because nature-based solutions can significantly contribute to Indonesia's climate commitments under the Paris Agreement.\par \par \uc2 Governance of such projects is also crucial to ensure the project's socio-environmental and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  impacts, as well as achieving the targets set by stakeholders.\par \par \uc2 NbS also still face several challenges in their funding and sustainability. These include limited funding availability, short-term funding cycles, lack of financial incentives, high initial costs, perceived risks and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , complex funding mechanisms, lack of awareness and understanding, \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and regulatory barriers, monitoring and evaluation costs and project scalability.\par \par \uc2 Regulatory and \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  obstacles, such as conflicting laws and supporting structures, may make the investment climate unfavorable to NbS.\par \par \uc2 Innovative financing methods, greater \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  awareness and education, enabling \b \highlight22\uc2 legislative\b0 \highlight\uc2  frameworks, cooperative efforts between \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  and private sector investors and civil society organizations are required to address these issues.\par \par \uc2 Nature-based solutions offer a sustainable approach to addressing environmental and social challenges in Indonesia. The country can boost resilience, encourage biodiversity and assist sustainable development by utilizing its natural ecosystems.\par \par \uc2 Holistic coordination between the government, local communities and stakeholders is necessary for the successful implementation of NbS, as this would guarantee the integration of such projects into larger development and \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  frameworks.\par \par \uc2 ___________________\par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Public policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  analyst at Mandiri Institute\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020240611ek6c0000j\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
