missions as well as sport models.\par \par \uc2 "Initially, many expected the local auto market to recover gradually, but shock after shock has negatively impacted the industry."\par \par \uc2 In terms of exports, local motorcycle producers saw a 9.79 percent yoy drop in shipments during the first five months of this year to 197,379 units.\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, carmakers have struggled to maintain sales this year with the automobile industry experiencing a 21 percent yoy drop in sales to 334,969 units in the first five months of this year, according to Association of Indonesian Automotive Manufacturers Association (Gaikindo) wholesale data.\par \par \uc2 Automobile expert Bebin Djuana said on June 10 that the drop in car sales was caused by several factors, namely the prolonged \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  of the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the weakening of the rupiah exchange rate against the United States dollar and a hike in the benchmark interest rate. He added that the impact has spilled over to the used car market as well.\par \par \uc2 "Initially, many expected the local auto market to recover gradually, but shock after shock has negatively impacted the industry," he said, as quoted from Kontan.\par \par \uc2 Rizwan Alamsjah, cochairman of Gaikindo, said on June 12 that automakers remain adamant that they can still achieve this year's target of selling 1.1 million units.\par \par \uc2 He argued that as long as the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is growing by 5 percent, then it is safe to assume that the household consumption trend will remain stable, and therefore auto sales as well.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020240618ek6j0000e\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
