\par\par \b \uc2 Unclear  \highlight22\uc2 fiscal policy \highlight\uc2  depressing rupiah: BI\b0\par\par\uc2 701 \uc2 words\par \uc2 21 June 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 11\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2024 The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2 The Jakarta Post,\par \par \uc2 Continued from page 1\par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI)\uc2  said it was confident the rupiah would return to Rp 15,900 per dollar in the long run, banking on the country's solid \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals.\par \par \uc2 "Our inflation is lower compared to the US and other countries, our \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  grew at much faster rate, and the yield on our bonds is also more attractive," BI governor \uc2 Perry Warjiyo\uc2  said at a press briefing on Thursday.\par \par \uc2 The rupiah exchange rate, he said, was being affected by negative sentiment that increased the risk premium of the Indonesian market.\par \par \uc2 On the external side, that included \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  regarding when the \uc2 US Federal Reserve\uc2  would cut rates and heightened geopolitical tensions.\par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  eased the external pressure in April by raising the benchmark interest rate to 6.25 percent from the previous 6 percent, resulting in an influx of foreign funds that strengthened the rupiah.\par \par \uc2 "The [positive] trend continued until there was a significant demand from corporations needing to pay dividends in dollars. But there is this [negative] perception. It is not necessarily true. Don't believe it. It's perception regarding the sustainability of the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  [\b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the next administration]," Perry said.\par \par \uc2 Last week, \uc2 Bloomberg\uc2  reported that Prabowo planned to fund his campaign programs by gradually increasing the debt-to-gross domestic product (GDP) ratio in the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  from 39 percent to 50 percent by the end of his presidency, citing sources familiar with the matter.\par \par \uc2 Thomas Djiwandono, who leads \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  discussions between Prabowo's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team and the outgoing government, denied that the president-elect had set any target for debt levels. He said the new administration would adhere to the legal limits on \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  metrics.\par \par \uc2 "We are not talking about debt-to-GDP target at all. This is not a formal \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  plan," said Thomas, who is also Prabowo's nephew, on Wednesday.\par \par \uc2 BI said demand for dollars from local corporations would decrease in the third quarter, reducing pressure on the rupiah.\par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  has decided to keep its benchmark rate unchanged in June amid expectations that it could make another hike sometime later this year to ease pressure on the currency.\par \par \uc2 For now, BI has said it will maintain the currency by performing market interventions and raising the yield on BI rupiah-denominated securities (SRBI) to attract foreign inflows.\par \par \uc2 Fikri C. Permana, an economist at KB Valbury Sekuritas, said the lack of clarity on the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  direction of the incoming administration had weighed on the rupiah.\par \par \uc2 He noted that investors typically preferred to move their money to countries with clearer \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  plans, such as India, which also held elections this year.\par \par \uc2 "In general, people around the world are trying to evade risks, so the fear is at a high level. Worries about \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  risks in the new administration make the fear even bigger," Fikri told The Jakarta Post on Thursday.\par \par \uc2 He suggested that the Finance Ministry and Prabowo's transition team communicate the incoming government's \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  more clearly.\par \par \uc2 Bhima Yudhistira, executive director at the Center of \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Law Studies (Celios), said \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  about incoming government's plan to raise the debt-to-GDP ratio and \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  to fund campaign promises was perceived as \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  a credibility issue by investors, which caused many to flee the country's financial markets.\par \par \uc2 He predicted that the rupiah might continue to weaken until September, before Prabowo's inauguration in October, as investors awaited clarity on the next administration's \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 "There must be a firm [statement], such as 'there will be cut on the free meal program'. That way, investors could be calmer because they would be sure there would be discipline in the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," Bhima told the Post on Wednesday.\par \par \uc2 Drajad Wibowo, a senior campaign aide to Prabowo, acknowledged that even though the campaign team had denied rumors of a potential debt-to-GDP ratio hike, the damage had already been done.\par \par \uc2 He told the Post on Thursday that the Finance Ministry, BI and the transition team should spread more "positive news" in order to calm the market.\par \par \uc2 The Finance Ministry was not immediately available for comment.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020240620ek6l00007\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
