\par\par \b \uc2 Rupiah Expected to Weaken Further to 16.510 per US Dollar\b0\par\par\uc2 298 \uc2 words\par \uc2 24 June 2024\par \uc2 Tempo.co\par \uc2 TEMPOE\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. PT Tempo Inti Media, Tbk \par \par \uc2 TEMPO.CO, Jakarta - The rupiah is expected to depreciate further against the US dollar today, June 24, according to Laba Forexindo Berjangka director Ibrahim Assuaibi. In last Friday's trading, the rupiah closed at 16,450 per US dollar, down from 16,438 on Thursday, June 20, 2024.\par \par \uc2 "The rupiah exchange rate is likely to fluctuate and close lower in the range of Rp16,440 - Rp16,510," Ibrahim said in his routine analysis.\par \par \uc2 Ibrahim said the market continues to monitor \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  direction \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which increases \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  risks. This is also a factor influencing the weakening of the rupiah currency. This can be seen from the projected condition of a large \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the range of 2.8 percent of GDP, which is inching towards the upper limit of 3 percent to GDP.\par \par \uc2 "In addition, news has recently surfaced about President-elect \uc2 Prabowo Subianto\uc2 's seemingly permissive attitude towards debt, with rumors even suggesting that he wanted to raise the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  debt ratio to around 50 percent of GDP, although this news was later denied by the Prabowo-Gibran team," he said.\par \par \uc2 Ibrahim suggested that the Prabowo-Gibran administration promptly communicate its commitment to \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  discipline in order to curb the rise in \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  risks and prevent negative sentiment towards the rupiah.\par \par \uc2 The government and \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  should maintain the currency's stability based on the fundamental strength of the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , he said. This means a trade balance surplus, not foreign exchange intervention with limited foreign exchange \b \highlight22\uc2 reserves\b0 \highlight\uc2  or raising domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 ANNISA FEBIOLA\par \par \uc2 Editor's Choice: Jokowi Gathers Financial Committee to Discuss Weakening Rupiah Today\par \par \uc2 Click here to get the latest news updates from Tempo on Google News\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://statik.tempo.co/data/2024/06/20/id_1311807/1311807_720.jpg"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Click here to view picture}}}\par \par \uc2 Document TEMPOE0020240624ek6o0005n\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
