\par\par \b \uc2 Prabowo's Free Meal Plan Stirs Investor Fears About Indonesia's Finances\b0\par\par\uc2 827 \uc2 words\par \uc2 13 July 2024\par \uc2 Tempo.co\par \uc2 TEMPOE\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. PT Tempo Inti Media, Tbk \par \par \uc2 TEMPO.CO, Jakarta - Indonesia's President-elect \uc2 Prabowo Subianto\uc2  wants to give school children free meals, but the plan and his pledge to be 'daring' on \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  have the country's debt and currency markets on edge.\par \par \uc2 Prabowo and his team have tried to distance themselves from any suggestions of \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  profligacy and to assure market participants the incoming government respects the legal debt limits that cap its \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  at 3% of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  output.\par \par \uc2 But for a market just getting accustomed to stability and recognition for \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  prudence under current Finance Minister Sri \uc2 Mulyani Indrawati\uc2 , the mere suggestion of heavy \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  has been unsettling.\par \par \uc2 Bond yields have risen and the rupiah has depreciated, though the currency weakness has largely been due to a resilient U.S. dollar.\par \par \uc2 "Our base case remains that this is more of noise at the moment, but we do see increasing \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  risk and hence the market may start to require more risk premium on Indonesian government bonds," said Jenny Zeng, chief investment officer for APAC fixed income at \uc2 Allianz Global Investors\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 "Also another risk is because there\u8217\'20\'19s a change of ministers," Zeng said, referring to \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  about who will step into the shoes of the highly acclaimed ex-\uc2 World Bank\uc2  managing director Sri Mulyani.\par \par \uc2 A banker at a Chinese lender in Indonesia said the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  concerns had prompted it to move around 30% of its portfolio into lower-tenor instruments, including diversifying into rupiah-denominated short-term securities (SRBI) issued by \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Prabowo won the election in February but will take office only in October. His free-meal plan, which his team estimates will cost 71 trillion rupiah or US$4.35 billion (with an assumed exchange rate of Rp16,330 to the US dollar) in 2025, should ordinarily not cause any consternation.\par \par \uc2 Southeast Asia's biggest country has seen its finances improve under the Jokowi administration and runs a small \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 . From being rated junk at the start of the century, its bonds are now regarded as investment grade.\par \par \uc2 Some investors even see merit in Indonesia \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  more to achieve its 8% \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth target. Yet there's unease over how much money Prabowo intends to spend on his programs, and whether he will cut fuel and other \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  and investments in order to balance the books.\par \par \uc2 "It appears there will be more \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  than certainty. I still stay invested but probably not as overweight as I used to be," said Clifford Lau, a portfolio manager at William Blair.\par \par \uc2 Foreign portfolio investments have been shrinking, with overseas investors pulling US$2.8 billion from rupiah government bonds and its stock market until June this year.\par \par \uc2 The rupiah is at four-year lows against the dollar, with losses of more than 5% this year, although most of that has been in line with the broad decline in emerging market currencies owing to rising U.S. yields and a rising dollar.\par \par \uc2 Investors seeking higher-yielding bonds have also been switching to India, whose bonds not only have comparable yields but have also just made it into \uc2 JP Morgan\uc2 's global index.\par \par \uc2 The selling has sent yields on Indonesia's 10-year bonds up 35 basis points since late May, to 7.05%.\par \par \uc2 IT'S NOT ALL BAD\par \par \uc2 Some investors are giving Prabowo the benefit of the doubt, pointing to how his administration also plans to increase revenues, improve \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  compliance, and cap the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  at 2.8% of GDP, even if higher than this year's 2.3% target.\par \par \uc2 "He\u8217\'20\'19s also talking about the need to increase \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue ... so it\u8217\'20\'19s actually not entirely about increasing expenses," \uc2 Abrdn\uc2 's investment manager of Asia fixed income, Jerome Tay, said. Tay is overweight and positive on Indonesian government bonds in the medium term.\par \par \uc2 Those bonds have long been a favorite among emerging market investors for their 'carry' or high yield.\par \par \uc2 The spread between Indonesian and U.S. bond yields is currently half the 600 basis points it used to be before the \uc2 Federal Reserve\uc2  started raising rates in 2022, nonetheless, they are still attractive for fixed-income investors.\par \par \uc2 The country is also now less vulnerable, given foreign holdings account for only 14% of outstanding government bonds. They used to own half the bonds a decade ago.\par \par \uc2 Expectations that the Fed will soon begin cutting rates are of some comfort to rupiah and Indonesian bond investors, Rudiyanto, a director at local asset management Panin said.\par \par \uc2 But other risks loom, notably huge debt maturities at around 800 trillion rupiah in 2025, nearly double that this year, although Sri Mulyani has said refinancing will not be a problem, provided the government maintains market confidence.\par \par \uc2 REUTERS\par \par \uc2 Editor's Choice: Al-Azhar Grand Imam Meets President-Elect \uc2 Prabowo Subianto\uc2 , Discuss Potential Defense Relations\par \par \uc2 Click here to get the latest news updates from Tempo on Google News\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://statik.tempo.co/data/2024/06/01/id_1306844/1306844_720.jpg"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Click here to view picture}}}\par \par \uc2 Document TEMPOE0020240712ek7d000mb\par }\page {\par\fs20\uc2 Business\par \b \uc2 Analysts Assess Impact of Trump Shooting on Indonesian Financial Markets\b0\par\par\uc2 627 \uc2 words\par \uc2 15 July 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Globe\par \uc2 JGLOBE\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. PT Jakarta Globe Media. \par \par \uc2 Jakarta. The failed assassination attempt on former US President \uc2 Donald Trump\uc2  has caused \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  in financial markets, including Indonesia. Analysts predict government bond yields to rise, while equity investors may become more cautious.\par \par \uc2 "This incident could boost Trump's popularity and increase his chances of winning the upcoming election," said Pasardana co-founder Hans Kwee on Sunday.\par \par \uc2 Kwee noted that financial markets generally do not favor a Trump victory in the presidential election. His aggressive trade policies could disrupt the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , and his strong pro-Israel stance might escalate tensions in the Middle East, leading to higher oil prices and inflation. However, Trump\u8217\'20\'19s support for Russia could potentially end the Russia-Ukraine war, lowering Russian gas prices in Europe and reducing coal prices.\par \par \uc2 On the impact of the Trump shooting on the Indonesian stock market, Kwee emphasized that this sentiment needs to be monitored further to determine if it will have a long-term effect. "If it has a long-term impact, meaning Trump\u8217\'20\'19s popularity continues to rise, the market might start to correct. However, in the short term, people will be more cautious, and corrections are very likely," he said.\par \par \uc2 Kwee is confident that the Trump incident will not affect the \uc2 Federal Reserve\uc2 's decision on the interest rate. "US inflation data was quite low, with unemployment at 4.1 percent, so the \uc2 Federal Reserve\uc2  is likely to cut by 25 basis points in September. Especially with the US election in November, there is a high chance of a rate cut then," he added.\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, government bond yields (SUN) are expected to increase to 6.8 percent-7.2 percent for 10-year tenors this week, slightly higher than the previous week's close of 6.944 percent, according to Pefindo Fixed Income Analyst Ahmad Nasrudin.\par \par \uc2 "I expect the bond market to be under pressure due to increasing negative external sentiment. Geopolitical risks, such as the Trump shooting and rising tensions in Taiwan, will influence the market," explained Ahmad on Monday.\par \par \uc2 Tokyo\u8217\'20\'19s latest defense white paper warns of increasing risks from China, North Korea, and Russia. "Foreign investors tend to be more cautious and speculative in emerging markets, including Indonesia," Ahmad added.\par \par \uc2 Markets are also awaiting speeches from Federal Reserve Chair \uc2 Jerome Powell\uc2  on the direction of US monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the \uc2 European \b \highlight22\uc2 Central Bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  (\uc2 ECB\uc2 ) meeting.\par \par \uc2 In Asia, attention is on the third plenary session of the Chinese Communist Party and potential major \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  reforms. China's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth is expected to slow, and policies related to the medium-term lending facility from the \uc2 People\u8217\'20\'19s Bank of China\uc2  will be closely watched.\par \par \uc2 "Geopolitical sentiment and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  data will influence the performance of domestic bond markets this week. I expect yields to move slightly upwards, assuming stronger geopolitical sentiment than positive \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  data releases," he said.\par \par \uc2 World shares began the week trading mixed and US futures were higher after the shooting incident.\par \par \uc2 Markets seemed to take in stride the shooting at Trump\u8217\'20\'19s rally in Butler, Pennsylvania that is being investigated as an attempted assassination of the presumptive Republican nominee.\par \par \uc2 Shares in \uc2 Trump Media & Technology Group Corp.\uc2  jumped sharply in pre-market trading Monday, gaining as much as 70 percent. They were up 52 percent at $46.92 a share on the Nasdaq as of 6 a.m. local time in New York.\par \par \uc2 Germany\u8217\'20\'19s DAX edged 0.1 percent lower to 18,721.84 and the CAC 40 in Paris declined 0.4 percent to 7,697.04. In London, the FTSE 100 was down 0.1 percent at 8,249.02.\par \par \uc2 The futures for the S&P 500 and Dow Jones Industrial Average were 0.4 percent higher.\par \par \uc2 Document JGLOBE0020240715ek7f00008\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
