\par\par \b \uc2 Analysts cut forecasts for IDX Composite amid  \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty \highlight\b0\par\par\uc2 Aditya Hadi, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \uc2 841 \uc2 words\par \uc2 22 July 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 2\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2024 The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2 Local and global brokerages are slashing their expectations for the \uc2 Indonesia Stock Exchange\uc2  (IDX) Composite amid a deteriorating outlook on companies' earnings following concerns over the incoming government's policies and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's interest rate cut.\par \par \uc2 Early this year, many brokerages expected the IDX Composite, a benchmark for the country's stock exchange, to increase to a record high of 8,000 points by the year-end.\par \par \uc2 Mandiri Sekuritas\uc2 , the securities arm of state-owned lender \uc2 Bank Mandiri\uc2 , had forecast that the index could reach 8,030 in a bullish scenario.\par \par \uc2 It cited a price-to-earnings (PE) ratio of Indonesian stocks at 15.1 points, much lower than Japan's 24.5 and India's 23.5, making it attractive to global investors.\par \par \uc2 The PE ratio tells investors whether a stock price accurately reflects any company's earning potential. A low ratio could indicate the price was lower than the company's actual worth, dubbed undervalued, while a high ratio could indicate overvaluation.\par \par \uc2 The IDX Composite peaked at around 7,433 in March from last year's around 7,200, but has been moving sideways since then. It was closed at 7,294 on Friday's trade, or 1.87 percent below its highest point.\par \par \uc2 Andre Benas, head of research at private lender \uc2 BCA\uc2 's securities arm, told The Jakarta Post on Tuesday that it projected the IDX Composite would hover between 7,200 and 7,300, much lower than its previous estimates of between 7,600 and 7,700.\par \par \uc2 He cited that low inflation indicated weak purchasing power among Indonesians, especially among low-income earners, which would imply companies' earnings were stagnating.\par \par \uc2 Even though earnings from publicly listed banks were at a high level, he expects they would not grow more than 15 percent this year, with some only seeing single-digit growth.\par \par \uc2 Mirae Asset Sekuritas, another local brokerage, also lowered its projection for the IDX Composite this year to 7,585 points from previously 8,100.\par \par \uc2 It attributed the worsening projection to the fact that \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI)\uc2  had not slashed \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  as aggressively as it predicted, citing that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  would only make 50 basis points (bps) cut this year instead of 100.\par \par \uc2 The BI rate hovered at 6.25 percent on Wednesday, which remained unchanged after the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  made a 25 bps hike in April.\par \par \uc2 "This affects our \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth projections," Rully Arya Wisnubroto, chief economist at Mirae Asset Sekuritas, said to the Post on Tuesday.\par \par \uc2 Rully pointed out that Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was expected to grow by 5.01 percent this year, much lower than the expected 5.12 percent. Similarly, next year's growth is projected to weaken at 5.02 percent, from the previously projected 5.34 percent.\par \par \uc2 The move of the local brokerages aligns with global brokerages that had lowered their ratings for the Indonesian market earlier.\par \par \uc2 In June, \uc2 Morgan Stanley\uc2  downgraded Indonesian equities to "underweight", citing risks in the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and a strong US dollar.\par \par \uc2 The lender pointed to president-elect \uc2 Prabowo Subianto\uc2 's campaign pledges, including his flagship free lunch program, which may impose a "substantial \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  burden" on the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 "We see near-term \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the direction of the future \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  stance as well as some weakness in the foreign exchange market amid still high US rates and a firm US dollar outlook," \uc2 Morgan Stanley\uc2 's strategists, including Asia and Emerging Market Equity Strategist Daniel Blake, wrote in the June 10 note.\par \par \uc2 Prabowo is reportedly planning to fund his programs by gradually increasing the debt-to-GDP ratio in the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  from 39 to 50 percent by the end of his presidency, a claim that Thomas Djiwandono of Prabowo's transition team has denied.\par \par \uc2 Another global lender \uc2 HSBC\uc2  also downgraded the prospects of the Indonesian stock market from "overweight" to "neutral", noting that earnings were being hit by high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  and a weak currency.\par \par \uc2 The lender also mentioned \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  surrounding government policies amid potential changes to the cabinet as one of the reasons.\par \par \uc2 BCA\uc2 's Andre suggested the upcoming government focus on boosting the country's purchasing power, including by creating more jobs and refraining from raising \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  that may squeeze middle-income earners.\par \par \uc2 "Wealth multipliers, especially for less educated people, are still in the labor-intensive sectors," Andre explained.\par \par \uc2 The government would also need to provide a clearer \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  direction that focused on easing red tape for foreign investors and directing state \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  to programs that could increase purchasing power.\par \par \uc2 Herditya Wicaksana, an analyst at local brokerage firm MNC Sekuritas, said on July 9 that the performance of the IDX Composite would depend on the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  of the next government and when the \uc2 United States Federal Reserve\uc2  cut \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as quoted from Bisnis.com.\par \par \uc2 On Wednesday, BI assessed that the US Fed would only begin its rate cut in November, much later than the market's expectations.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020240721ek7m00007\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
