\par\par \b \uc2 Banks vie for deposits in high-rate environment\b0\par\par\uc2 716 \uc2 words\par \uc2 27 July 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 11\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2024 The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2 The Jakarta Post,\par \par \uc2 Continued from page 1\par \par \uc2 In an assessment published on July 17, BI noted that the increase in the \uc2 COF\uc2  was observed across all types of banks, including regional development banks (BPD), state-owned enterprise (SOE) banks and private banks, but that the situation varied from one bank to another.\par \par \uc2 Some banks more prepared than others\par \par \uc2 "Divergences in \uc2 COF\uc2  changes reflect different transmission timings of banks' responses to the rise in BI's benchmark rates, as well as varying liquidity conditions," the report states.\par \par \uc2 BRI, a major SOE bank, had achieved just 4 percent growth in third-party funds last year but was able to accelerate growth to 11.6 percent year-on-year (yoy) by the end of June, giving it more liquidity to disburse loans.\par \par \uc2 BRI beefed up its third-party funds with an 18.9 percent yoy rise in time deposits, which typically come with high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 . The lender's \uc2 COF\uc2  increased to 3.6 percent at the end of June from 2.7 percent a year earlier, indicating that the deposit growth was driven by higher rates offered.\par \par \uc2 BRI also saw an almost 20percent increase in current account deposits, which are used by firms to manage daily transactions and yield little or no interest. This aligns with BI data showing corporate customer savings increased by 20.7 percent during the period, while individual savings rose by only 1.7 percent.\par \par \uc2 Efdinal Alamsyah, compliance director at publicly listed Bank Oke, said the trend reflected a wait-and-see stance of corporations that may be reluctant to expand operations amid political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 "Thus, they may prefer to increase their savings in banks," he said on Wednesday, as quoted by Kontan.\par \par \uc2 However, the country's largest private bank, \uc2 BCA\uc2 , saw sluggish third-party funds growth of just 4.79 percent yoy at the end of June. The lender said it was under no pressure to increase savings \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  as its proportion of current and saving account assets, dubbed "cheap funds", stood at 82.2 percent, significantly above the industry average of 62.8 percent.\par \par \uc2 Despite tightening liquidity, \uc2 BCA\uc2  remains in a relatively strong position with a loan-to-deposit ratio of 74.72 percent in June, below the industry average of 84.5 percent.\par \par \uc2 "[Banks could maintain their profit] by focusing on high-yield\par \par \uc2 loan disbursement, cutting operational costs and offering new products,\par \par \uc2 for example, long-term savings with \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  higher than regular\par \par \uc2 savings but lower than time deposits."\par \par \uc2 Small banks exposed\par \par \uc2 A report from the Center of Reform on Economics (CORE) noted that the rising \uc2 COF\uc2  was affecting small banks with less than Rp 6 trillion (US$367.7 million) in core capital and where expensive time deposits typically account for the lion's share of third-party funds. While other banks attracted more savings, small banks saw a 5.9 percent yoy drop in third-party funds by the end of May.\par \par \uc2 "Banks should focus [on disbursing loans] in retail sectors to generate interest income that could offset the \uc2 COF\uc2  [rise]," suggested CORE senior researcher Etikah Karyani Suwondo on Thursday.\par \par \uc2 LPPI's Amin said the challenge for small banks was exacerbated by the emergence of new business models, such as financial technology and digital banks.\par \par \uc2 "[Banks could maintain their profit] by focusing on high-yield loan disbursement, cutting operational costs and offering new products, for example, long-term savings with \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  higher than regular savings but lower than time deposits," he told the Post on Friday.\par \par \uc2 Digital banks, despite being categorized as "small", still grew their third-party funds by offering high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  for savings and time deposits. They typically have wealthy investors who could inject liquidity, allowing them to offer such incentives.\par \par \uc2 Krom Bank, backed by buy now, pay later platform Kredivo, offers annual \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  between 6.5 and 7.25 percent for one-month time deposits. As a result, it quadrupled its time deposits over the past six months to Rp 1.27 trillion.\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, Superbank increased its savings account funds more than 24-fold to Rp 517.7 billion over the same period by offering 6 percent \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  on accounts connected to the on-demand platform Grab, one of its backers.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020240726ek7r0000c\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
