\par\par \uc2 BUSSINESS\par \b  \highlight22\uc2 POLICY \highlight\uc2  COORDINATION TO ADDRESS GLOBAL CHALLENGES AT G20 MEETING: BI\b0\par\par\uc2 526 \uc2 words\par \uc2 29 July 2024\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By Cindy Frishanti Octavia\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI)\uc2  emphasized the importance of \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  coordination in overcoming global challenges that overshadow the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  at the G20 Meeting held in Brazil.\par \par \uc2 BI drew attention to this aspect at the Third Meeting of Finance Ministers and \b \highlight22\uc2 Central Bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  Governors of the G20 countries (FMCBG) under the Brazilian Presidency, which was held on July 25-26, 2024, in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil.\par \par \uc2 "Global \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , such as monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  divergence and high \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  debt in several developed countries, has had an impact on the limited ability of developing countries to maintain \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  stability and growth," BI Governor \uc2 Perry Warjiyo\uc2  noted in an official statement in Jakarta, Monday.\par \par \uc2 Hence, Warjiyo called on developed countries to take steps to overcome the spillover of global challenges to developing countries.\par \par \uc2 The steps encompass strengthening the transparency of monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  to provide clarity on responses and \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  directions for actors in the financial sector, maintaining perceptions, and calming market reactions so as to strengthen global stability.\par \par \uc2 Other necessary actions are implementing measures to reduce excessive debt levels and implementing a more prudent sustainable \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as well as strengthening coordination of \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary policies and structural reforms to increase productivity.\par \par \uc2 At the meeting, the ministers and \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  governors of the G20 members agreed that the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is growing resiliently but is still overshadowed by \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  that have the potential to disrupt medium-term growth prospects.\par \par \uc2 Hence, the G20 agreed to optimize international cooperation.\par \par \uc2 In the financial sector, the ministers and \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  governors viewed that the resilience of the global financial system remains maintained, supported by solid regulations and supervision.\par \par \uc2 In the future, efforts to strengthen resilience on the operational side need to continue to be a concern in line with the increasing use of digital technology.\par \par \uc2 BI emphasized the importance of comprehensive risk assessments, good governance, effective cyber incident handling and recovery planning, and the availability of technology and infrastructure capable of mitigating risks.\par \par \uc2 The Third Meeting of the G20 FMCBG under the Brazilian Presidency continued discussions on various important agendas under the main theme of the Presidency, "Building a Just World and a Sustainable Planet".\par \par \uc2 Topics discussed included the global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  outlook and ongoing global challenges, the financial sector and financial inclusion, international \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  cooperation, climate change, financing for sustainable development, capital flows and global debt.\par \par \uc2 Furthermore, in the discussion related to the financial inclusion agenda, Indonesia welcomed the progress of the G20 Global Partnership for Financial Inclusion (GPFI) in encouraging progress in \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and financial inclusion.\par \par \uc2 Indonesia conveyed that during the 2022 Indonesian Presidency, BI emphasized three approaches to encourage financial inclusion, comprising increasing access to and use of financial products and services to develop MSMEs and improve \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  welfare, including through financial literacy and consumer protection.\par \par \uc2 The other steps include the implementation of macroprudential policies to encourage liquidity in credit distribution coordinated with \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the digitalization of payment systems with the support of digital financial infrastructure and cooperation on payment systems between countries.\par \par \uc2 (T.C009/A/A063/A063) 29-07-2024 12:41:28\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020240729ek7t0005l\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
