\par\par \uc2 BUSSINESS\par \b \uc2 INDONESIA ENCOURAGES COOPERATION IN  \highlight22\uc2 ECONOMY \highlight\uc2 , CLIMATE AT G20 BRAZIL\b0\par\par\uc2 342 \uc2 words\par \uc2 29 July 2024\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - Indonesian Finance Minister \uc2 Sri Mulyani Indrawati\uc2  called for global collaboration on handling \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  challenges and climate change during the Third Meeting of G20 Finance Ministers and \b \highlight22\uc2 Central Bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  Governors held in Brazil.\par \par \uc2 As cited from her office"s statement received here on Monday, Indrawati remarked that global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  induced by geopolitical tensions, monetary fluctuations, and elections had led to increased market volatility and hampered investments.\par \par \uc2 On that note, the minister pointed to the need for macroeconomic policies that can address inequality, the impacts of fluctuations in exchange rates and \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 , and medium-term \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  effects.\par \par \uc2 She then proposed implementing the debt-for-climate swap scheme that allows countries with low \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  capacity to swap debts they owe for commitments to mobilizing funds for eco-friendly initiatives.\par \par \uc2 Indonesia has resorted to the scheme by swapping its responsibility to pay US$35 million in debts for a commitment to disbursing the same amount of funds for the protection of coral reefs.\par \par \uc2 "Indonesia will strengthen its national biodiversity financing framework and continuously bridge gaps in the financing of biodiversity conservation and utilization," she stated.\par \par \uc2 In addition to the debt-for-climate swap, the Indonesian state treasurer also pushed for the formulation of integrated strategies to boost development financing, with the aim of pursuing the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs).\par \par \uc2 She then drew attention to international \b \highlight22\uc2 taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2 , highlighting the need for a more fair \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  imposition on wealthy people.\par \par \uc2 "Effective, progressive policies are required to narrow down income and wealth disparities. It is also necessary to promote information exchange to prevent people with high incomes from committing aggressive \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  planning," she emphasized.\par \par \uc2 Furthermore, Indrawati emphasized the urgency of reforming multilateral development banks (MDBs) to maintain their relevance and effectiveness.\par \par \uc2 "MDBs should also bolster the representation of developing countries, including by employing more staff from such countries, to implement effective projects and take local contexts and cultures into consideration," she remarked.\par \par \uc2 (T.KR-TEG/A/R013/R013) 29-07-2024 16:12:31\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020240729ek7t000m9\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
