\par\par \b \uc2 Indonesia's  \highlight22\uc2 Economic \highlight\uc2  Growth Lower to 5.05% in Q2 of 2024, BPS Reports\b0\par\par\uc2 352 \uc2 words\par \uc2 5 August 2024\par \uc2 Tempo.co\par \uc2 TEMPOE\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. PT Tempo Inti Media, Tbk \par \par \uc2 TEMPO.CO, Jakarta - Statistics Indonesia (BPS) reported that Indonesia\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in the second quarter of 2024 has reached 5.05 percent year-on-year (y-o-y), slightly lower than the first quarter\u8217\'20\'19s 5.11 percent.\par \par \uc2 Deputy for Balance Sheets and Statistical Analysis of BPS Muhammad Edy Mahmud said that growth remained stable as it was supported by strong \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity.\par \par \uc2 "The manufacturing industry contributes the biggest to the growth with 0.79 percent," he said on Monday, August 5, 2024.\par \par \uc2 In addition, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth was also supported by the construction business sector at 0.67 percent, trade at 0.63 percent, and information and communication at 0.50 percent.\par \par \uc2 Edy explained that since the first quarter of 2019, Indonesia\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  has grown alongside the seasonal pattern. The manufacturing industry grew supported by domestic and foreign demand. Meanwhile, the food and beverage industry is supported by Eid al-Fitr and Eid al-Adha, while the rice harvest drives the supply sector.\par \par \uc2 Previously, Macroeconomics and Financial Market Researcher at the Institute for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Community Research, Faculty of \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Business, University of Indonesia (LPEM FEB UI) Teuku Riefky projected that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth will be lower compared to the previous period.\par \par \uc2 Riefky said Indonesia\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will grow between 5.0 to 5.1 percent this year, led by the lack of seasonal driving factors and high domestic and global \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 On the other hand, Indonesia\u8217\'20\'19s first quarter was colored by a number of events from the February general elections, the fasting period, and several holidays. These, he said, boost domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity.\par \par \uc2 Although Indonesia entered 2024 with a positive \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth record, Riefky believed it was not a sign of fundamental \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  improvement. The issue with Indonesia\u8217\'20\'19s \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth is the seasonal-driven growth which indicates structural problems.\par \par \uc2 ILONA ESTHERINA\par \par \uc2 Editor\u8217\'20\'19s Choice: Jokowi Reminds Prabowo of \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Risks in 2025 \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  Meeting\par \par \uc2 Click here to get the latest news updates from Tempo on Google News\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://statik.tempo.co/data/2023/08/15/id_1228235/1228235_720.jpg"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Click here to view picture}}}\par \par \uc2 Document TEMPOE0020240805ek85000gq\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
