\par\par \b \uc2 Economists, business groups raise alarm over purchasing power\b0\par\par\uc2 463 \uc2 words\par \uc2 10 August 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 11\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2024 The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2 The Jakarta Post,\par \par \uc2 Continued from page 1\par \par \uc2 The survey report published on Friday also shows that consumer expectations for \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  conditions in the next six months have weakened, with the Consumer Expectations Index falling from 133.8 in June to 133.3 in July. The decline was observed across all parameters, including income expectations, job opportunities and business prospects.\par \par \uc2 Josua Pardede, chief economist at private lender Bank Permata, highlighted several indicators of lower purchasing power, including a decline in new car sales, which are predicted to come in below 1 million this year, and household \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth lagging behind national \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth.\par \par \uc2 Based on those trends, he forecast a slowdown in \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in the second half that would push full-year gross domestic product (GDP) growth down to 5 percent this year, adding, however, that the situation might improve next year should household \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  rebound.\par \par \uc2 "Amid \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  global conditions, the government needs to strengthen consumption by conducting thorough studies before throwing [issues about] \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  plans to the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 , so [that there] will not be any negative effect on \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  [perceptions]," he said on Thursday, as quoted by Kompas.\par \par \uc2 Business players say they are feeling the pinch of weakening purchasing power.\par \par \