\par\par \uc2 INTERNATIONAL NEWS\par \b \uc2 ASEAN'S CRUCIAL ROLE AMID GLOBAL  \highlight22\uc2 UNCERTAINTY \highlight\b0\par\par\uc2 900 \uc2 words\par \uc2 10 August 2024\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By Katriana\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - As it enters its 57th year, the \uc2 Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN)\uc2  is assuming an increasingly important role amid ongoing global dynamics.\par \par \uc2 This important role, according to Foreign Affairs Minister \uc2 Retno Marsudi\uc2 , is reflected in the efforts made by \uc2 ASEAN\uc2  countries to jointly maintain regional peace, stability, and prosperity amid a global climate of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Further, the region is seen as relatively stable, given its firm \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth of 4.5 percent, higher than the global average.\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, as the ASEAN region grows into a global hub for technological innovation and trade, it is also expected to post more significant gross domestic product (GDP) growth, according to the \uc2 International Monetary Fund\uc2 "s (IMF"s) estimates.\par \par \uc2 However, Marsudi, in her speech at the 57th ASEAN anniversary event here on Thursday, highlighted the increasingly complex geopolitical situation.\par \par \uc2 This indicates more serious problems, such as a trust \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  between countries, a zero-sum paradigm, the erosion of multilateralism, and a lack of respect for international law.\par \par \uc2 To maintain peace and stability in the region, three important goals need to continue to be pursued, she said.\par \par \uc2 The first goal is making \uc2 ASEAN\uc2  a region that is fit for purpose, which will ensure that the \uc2 ASEAN\uc2  community remains the focus of development goals in the region.\par \par \uc2 To realize this, it will be necessary for \uc2 ASEAN\uc2  to affirm its commitment to advancing and protecting human rights.\par \par \uc2 The mechanism for handling human rights issues in \uc2 ASEAN\uc2  must keep up with the growing human rights challenges, especially in responding to the increasing number of human trafficking cases in the region and the serious human rights violations in Gaza, Palestine.\par \par \uc2 The second goal is to make \uc2 ASEAN\uc2  a region that is fit for challenges so that it can respond to existing problems.\par \par \uc2 To address challenges, the ASEAN Community Vision 2045 must include action-oriented strategic plans.\par \par \uc2 Regional mechanisms must be strengthened, in particular for health architecture, food and energy security, financial stability, and digital transformation.\par \par \uc2 "Only by doing so, we can ensure our region becomes the epicentrum of growth," Marsudi said.\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, the third goal is to make \uc2 ASEAN\uc2  a region that is fit for greatness. Inclusivity and a culture of collaboration are key to realizing peace, stability, and prosperity in the region.\par \par \uc2 Therefore, \uc2 ASEAN\uc2  needs to continue to mainstream this paradigm beyond \uc2 ASEAN\uc2 , through the ASEAN Outlook on the Indo-Pacific (AOIP).\par \par \uc2 A connected and resilient ASEAN\par \par \uc2 In line with Marsudi, who underlined the importance of the collaboration paradigm, ASEAN Secretary-General Kao Kim Hourn also emphasized the importance of unity and cooperation to improve connectivity and resilience in the region.\par \par \uc2 All of this could help realize an \uc2 ASEAN\uc2  that is increasingly connected and resilient, in accordance with the theme of the 57th anniversary of the grouping this year.\par \par \uc2 Underlining ASEAN"s commitment to fostering regional integration, cooperation, and interconnectivity, the secretary general stressed three key points that are currently his focus.\par \par \uc2 The first is that \uc2 ASEAN\uc2  must continue to uphold the principle of open regionalism, ensure its neutrality and unity, as well as maintain market openness to trade and investment.\par \par \uc2 He said that the involvement of ASEAN countries at the global level is very important to promote peace, security, stability, and prosperity in the region.\par \par \uc2 In addition, \uc2 ASEAN\uc2  needs to maintain an open, inclusive, and rules-based regional order to enhance progress in a dynamic international landscape.\par \par \uc2 The second crucial point is that \uc2 ASEAN\uc2  must unlock all potentials that drive new growth to diversify the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and increase resilience.\par \par \uc2 Hence, \uc2 ASEAN\uc2  countries need to take advantage of the digital \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the dynamics of a young, tech-savvy population, and the adoption of innovative technologies must continue to be pursued.\par \par \uc2 It is essential to implement effective digitization initiatives, including the ASEAN digital \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  framework, negotiations on which are targeted to be completed next year.\par \par \uc2 The secretary-general said he hopes that the innovative agreement will make a significant contribution to the development of digital \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in ASEAN region, bridge the regional digital divide, increase productivity and competitiveness, and ultimately, improve the welfare of people throughout theregion.\par \par \uc2 The third important point is ensuring the implementation of the \uc2 ASEAN\uc2  people"s pillar by making people the main motivation for regional integration, he said.\par \par \uc2 "This is to ensure that it provides real benefits to our people and society," he added.\par \par \uc2 The 57th anniversary celebration of ASEAN at the ASEAN Secretariat in Jakarta on Thursday raised the theme of a connected and resilient ASEAN community.\par \par \uc2 The celebration was opened by ASEAN Secretary-General Hourn, Minister Marsudi, and Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign Minister of Lao PDR, Saleumxay Kommasith.\par \par \uc2 The event was also attended by Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Affairs, \uc2 Airlangga Hartarto\uc2 , and Minister of Agrarian Affairs and Spatial Planning and head of the National Land Agency (ATR/BPN), Agus Harimurti Yudhoyono, as well as ambassadors from several countries.\par \par \uc2 The event also lauded Minister Marsudi for her decade of dedication to Indonesia as foreign minister, and her support for ASEAN, especially the ASEAN Secretariat.\par \par \uc2 During the celebration, Indonesia also presented collaborative batik from Indonesia for ASEAN with batik motifs inspired by the diversity of flowers that grow in ASEAN countries.\par \par \uc2 The collaborative batik symbolized hope, wisdom, and solidarity, as well as synergy between countries in Southeast Asia.\par \par \uc2 (T.K012/A/Y012/Y012) 10-08-2024 09:26:05\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020240810ek8a0002t\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
