\par\par \b \uc2 IMF Projects Indonesia's  \highlight22\uc2 Economy \highlight\uc2  to Stagnate at 5.1% Despite Prabowo's 8% Growth Ambition\b0\par\par\uc2 515 \uc2 words\par \uc2 13 August 2024\par \uc2 Tempo.co\par \uc2 TEMPOE\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. PT Tempo Inti Media, Tbk \par \par \uc2 TEMPO.CO, Jakarta - The \uc2 International Monetary Fund\uc2  (\uc2 IMF\uc2 ) projects that Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth will stagnate at 5 to 5.1 percent in 2024-2029. The forecast contrasts with the 8 percent \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth target promised by president-elect \uc2 Prabowo Subianto\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 In its 2024 Country Report Issue 270, the \uc2 IMF\uc2  predicts that Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth will rise to a range of 5 to 5.1 percent in 2024-2025, followed by stagnation at an annual range of 5.1 percent between 2025 and 2029.\par \par \uc2 "Growth would reach 5.0 and 5.1 percent in 2024 and 2025, respectively, with dynamic domestic demand offsetting the drag from weaker commodity prices," the report said, as quoted by Tempo on Tuesday, Aug. 13.\par \par \uc2 The report also stated that "The authorities are more optimistic about growth compared to the staff's projections. They believe that a range of 4.7-5.5% in 2024 and 4.8-5.6% in 2025 is attainable, driven mainly by domestic demand."\par \par \uc2 However, the \uc2 IMF\uc2  said there is optimism that medium-term growth will rise to 6-7% annually, driven by \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  transformation through structural reforms aimed at achieving the 2045 Golden Indonesia Vision. "This includes comprehensive efforts to enhance human capital, continue developing infrastructure, and improve the business and investment climate."\par \par \uc2 Prabowo confident of 8 percent \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth\par \par \uc2 On the other hand, President-elect \uc2 Prabowo Subianto\uc2  believes that Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  can grow at a higher rate during his five-year term. "For me, I am optimistic that we can reach 8 percent," Prabowo said in a speech at the launch of the One One Map \b \highlight22\uc2 Policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Geoportal in Jakarta last month.\par \par \uc2 In fact, Prabowo is confident that the Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will be able to achieve growth of up to 8 percent in the next two to three years, as he said when he attended the Qatar \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Forum 2024 in Doha in May, accompanied by Vice President-elect Gibran Rakabuming Raka.\par \par \uc2 "I'm very confident, I've talked to experts and studied the numbers. I'm sure we can get to 8 percent easily. I'm determined to surpass that," he said in Doha,\par \par \uc2 Prabowo said Indonesia could easily achieve \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth of 8 percent within 2 to 3 years.\par \par \uc2 According to government data earlier this month, Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  grew at an annual rate of 5.11 percent in the January-March period, the highest in three quarters.\par \par \uc2 Prabowo said he would uphold the tradition of prudent \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  management, saying he intended to keep the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  limit at 3 percent of gross domestic product (GDP).\par \par \uc2 "This is about refocusing and reducing waste, reducing allocations to non-essential activities," he said. "I think now is the time to be more daring in implementing good governance."\par \par \uc2 Raden Putri, Riani Sanusi, Daniel A Fajri\par \par \uc2 Editor's Choice: \uc2 IMF\uc2  Declares Indonesia 'A Source of Hope' Amid Global \b \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainty\b0 \highlight\par \par \uc2 Click here to get the latest news updates from Tempo on Google News\par \par