\par\par \uc2 INTERNATIONAL NEWS\par \b \uc2 APEC\uc2  BOOSTS COOPERATION IN LOW-CARBON HYDROGEN AS CLEAN ENERGY CARRIER\b0\par\par\uc2 587 \uc2 words\par \uc2 14 August 2024\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By Yuni Arisandy Sinaga\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - \uc2 APEC\uc2  member economies are intensifying cooperation to harness the power of clean and low-carbon hydrogen as a key component of the region\u8217\'20\'19s sustainable energy future.\par \par \uc2 At a workshop hosted by APEC Peru 2024 in Lima, policymakers, industry leaders, and researchers shared best practices, discussed challenges, and explored opportunities for integrating hydrogen into the energy mix.\par \par \uc2 According to a statement issued by the APEC Energy Working Group on Wednesday, members are focused on creating roadmaps that set clear targets, establish market-driven indicators, and outline actionable steps to scale up clean and low-carbon hydrogen production.\par \par \uc2 "In the face of the short-term difficulties presented by the energy and climate crisis, our economies have assumed an increasingly decisive role in global trade and renewable energy supply chains," Peru\u8217\'20\'19s Minister of Energy and Mines, R\u243\'00\'F3mulo Mucho, remarked.\par \par \uc2 "At the same time, our economies face the challenge of a transition towards a more sustainable, resilient, and inclusive development,"" he stated.\par \par \uc2 Mucho noted that energy resources will, therefore, continue to play an essential role in contributing to the transition.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CA demand for secure, affordable, reliable, and sustainable energy will generate collaborative dynamics that drive our economies to overcome the challenges in our energy matrix," he stated.\par \par \uc2 A panel of experts discussed the implementation of projects aimed at transitioning from fossil fuels to clean energy sources.\par \par \uc2 The session highlighted the need for harmonized regulatory frameworks and innovative financing mechanisms to drive the adoption of hydrogen technologies, taking into account the other stages of the sector"s value chain: transport and electricity generation.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CDespite increased attention on clean and low-carbon hydrogen in recent years, its future viability as a clean, low-emission energy source remains \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2 ,\u8221\'20\'1D President of the Asia Pacific Energy Research Centre (APERC) Kazutomo Irie stated.\par \par \uc2 He pointed to cost competitiveness and the delay in infrastructure development among the key challenges that could prevent the widespread adoption of clean and low-carbon hydrogen.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CTechnological advancements, economies of scale, and cumulative production will reduce costs,\u8221\'20\'1D Irie explained.\par \par \uc2 "Until substantial cost reductions are realized, the commercial development of a clean, low-carbon hydrogen market will heavily rely on supportive government policies, including \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which vary widely among economies," he explained.\par \par \uc2 Participants also shared insights on developing domestic hydrogen strategies, emphasizing the importance of cross-border collaboration to achieve regional energy goals.\par \par \uc2 Representatives from China, Indonesia, Japan, Korea, Chinese Taipei, and Thailand provided diverse perspectives on the challenges and successes of hydrogen initiatives in each \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 A dedicated session underscored the critical role women play in the hydrogen and renewable energy sectors. Speakers explored how women are breaking barriers and shaping policies that promote sustainable practices and clean technologies.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1C\uc2 APEC\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s commitment to advancing hydrogen technologies reflects the region\u8217\'20\'19s leadership in promoting innovative solutions to global challenges and driving sustainable \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth,\u8221\'20\'1D lead shepherd for the APEC Energy Working Group Ariadne BenAissa stated.\par \par \uc2 The workshop concluded with a call to action for APEC economies to continue collaborating on hydrogen initiatives, ensuring that the region remains at the forefront of the global clean energy transition.\par \par \uc2 Furthermore, Mucho will host his counterparts for the APEC Energy Ministerial Meeting in Lima on August 15-16.\par \par \uc2 They will further deliberate on strategies and technologies to ensure just, inclusive, and sustainable energy transitions, as well as policies and actions for hydrogen development in APEC economies.\par \par \uc2 (T.Y012/B/A075/A075) 14-08-2024 15:26:25\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020240814ek8e0008d\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw177\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2655\pichgoal600
