\par\par \uc2 NATIONAL NEWS\par \b \uc2 INDONESIA'S  \highlight22\uc2 ECONOMIC \highlight\uc2  GROWTH REMAINS ABOVE GLOBAL AVERAGE: PRESIDENT\b0\par\par\uc2 314 \uc2 words\par \uc2 16 August 2024\par \uc2 LKBN ANTARA\par \uc2 ANTARA\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. LKBN Antara \par \par \uc2 By\par \par \uc2 Jakarta (ANTARA) - President Joko Widodo (Jokowi) reiterated that Indonesia has been successful in maintaining its \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth rate above that of the global average.\par \par \uc2 "Indonesia"s \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth has been consistently pegged at around five percent, surpassing the average global rate of 3.4 percent," he remarked during the presentation of the 2025 Draft State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  (RAPBN) and its financial notes at the Parliamentary Complex, Jakarta, on Friday.\par \par \uc2 The president praised Indonesians as people of a resilient nation able to brave a variety of tough global challenges in the last decade, such as the COVID-19 pandemic, geopolitical tensions, trade wars, crises, and climate change-induced disasters.\par \par \uc2 "Praise be to God, in the midst of those challenges and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , our political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  situations remain stable and even grow sustainably," he pointed out.\par \par \uc2 Jokowi then highlighted the addition of 21.3 million new workforce during the 2015-2024 period while spotlighting the fact that Indonesia"s debt ratio has been one of the lowest among member states of the \uc2 Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN)\uc2  and G20.\par \par \uc2 Moreover, the president highlighted that Indonesia"s export value had increased by over 70 percent, hitting US$259 billion last year. This positive trend is coupled with a surplus in trade balance in the last 51 months.\par \par \uc2 According to data from Statistics Indonesia (BPS), the export value in June 2024 stood at US$20.84 billion, with the manufacturing sector being the most significant contributor.\par \par \uc2 Earlier, on July 15, BPS Acting Head Amalia Adininggar Widyasanti revealed that during the period from January to June 2024, the export value of the manufacturing sector was registered at US$91.65 billion, thereby contributing as much as 73.27 percent to Indonesia"s total export value.\par \par \uc2 (T.KR-TEG/B/Y012/Y012) 16-08-2024 16:20:22\par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020240816ek8g000p1\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 Concerns over Mandatory Vehicle Third-Party Liability Insurance\b0\par\par\uc2 1,692 \uc2 words\par \uc2 16 August 2024\par \uc2 Tempo Magazine\par \uc2 TEMGEN\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. PT Tempo Inti Media, Tbk. \par \par \uc2 THE government\u8217\'20\'19s plan to mandate motor vehicle insurance next year has left Lili Pujiati feeling uneasy. Lili, who serves as the Chairperson of the Indonesian Transportation Workers Union, fears that the insurance requirement will add to the burden on her members, especially online motorcycle taxi and taxi drivers, as well as couriers.\par \par \uc2 According to Lili, their income is \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  and generally low, leaving little room to pay for insurance premiums. \u8220\'20\'1CDue to the partnership model, online transportation drivers do not earn a decent wage like other workers,\u8221\'20\'1D she said on Wednesday, August 7.\par \par \uc2 The government and the \uc2 Financial Services Authority (OJK)\uc2  are currently drafting a third-party liability (\uc2 TPL\uc2 ) insurance scheme, which would be mandatory for all motor vehicle owners by 2025. \uc2 TPL\uc2  insurance provides coverage for losses suffered by a third party, along with their claims against the vehicle owner, resulting from risks such as collisions, crashes, and other incidents.\par \par \uc2 The obligation to have motor vehicle insurance under the \uc2 TPL\uc2  scheme is mandated by Law No. 4/2023 on the Development and Strengthening of the Financial Sector (PPSK). Article 39A paragraph 1 of the law states that mandatory insurance programs are related to traffic accidents, fire insurance, and residential insurance against disaster risks.\par \par \uc2 With this scheme, motor vehicle owners and the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  should have \u8216\'20\'18protection\u8217\'20\'19 against potential incidents. However, the issue is that paying the insurance premium becomes a new burden for vehicle owners, especially those working in the informal sector. For example, Irwansyah, a 37-year-old online motorcycle taxi driver, is confused about how he would manage to pay the \uc2 TPL\uc2  insurance premium. With an income of Rp4 million (around US$250) per month, he feels that the insurance cost is too high. \u8220\'20\'1CI don\u8217\'20\'19t know where to set aside money for it,\u8221\'20\'1D he said.\par \par \uc2 A police officer managing traffic on Jalan Margonda, Depok, West Java, July 18. The government and the \uc2 Financial Services Authority (OJK)\uc2  are designing a third-party liability scheme that all motor vehicle owners must have by 2025. ANTARA/Yulius Satria Wijaya\par \par \uc2 The plan to mandate motor vehicle insurance has also caught the attention of the Indonesian Consumer Protection Foundation (YLKI). YLKI Executive Chair Agus Suyatno pointed out that poor communication from the government in conveying this idea, combined with the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s low literacy regarding insurance products, has only complicated matters. According to him, the government seems blind to the additional \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  burden this \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would impose if implemented. Never mind insurance, \u8220\'20\'1COut of 120 million motorcycles and 100 million cars in Indonesia, only 60 percent pay vehicle \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2 ,\u8221\'20\'1D he said.\par \par \uc2 Agus believes that the government should first address issues of transparency and the management of \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  funds, such as insurance, before rolling out a mandatory \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Moreover, he added, the reputation of the insurance industry has taken a hit following recent cases of defaults and fraud involving major companies like Asuransi Jiwasraya. \u8220\'20\'1C\b \highlight22\uc2 Public\b0 \highlight\uc2  complaints about insurance rank in the top 10 of the reports we receive at the YLKI each year,\u8221\'20\'1D he stated.\par \par \uc2 Ogi Prastomiyono, the Chief Executive of Insurance, Guarantee, and Pension Fund Supervision at the \uc2 Financial Services Authority (OJK)\uc2 , argued that the \uc2 TPL\uc2  insurance product would provide financial protection to the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the event of an accident and facing claims from the aggrieved party. According to Ogi, \uc2 TPL\uc2  insurance is different from the motor vehicle insurance schemes known to the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 , such as total loss only or all-risk coverage. Under the \uc2 TPL\uc2  scheme, compensation can be paid out without the need to first purchase motor vehicle insurance. \u8220\'20\'1CThis will reduce the social costs borne by the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  when accidents occur,\u8221\'20\'1D he explained.\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22\u8226\'20\'22\u8226\'20\'22\par \par \uc2 THE high number of traffic accidents and the associated losses are among the reasons the government is implementing mandatory third-party liability motor vehicle insurance. According to police data, in 2023, there were 150,000 accidents with material losses totaling Rp300 billion (US$18.8 million). The average loss per accident amounted to Rp2 million (US$125) per case.\par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, analysis by the OJK on voluntary \uc2 TPL\uc2  insurance products showed that the average claim for third parties between 2017 and 2021 ranged from Rp6 million to Rp10 million (US$376-626) per incident. A demographic analysis by Jasa Raharja on accident cases up to June 2024 found that 60 percent of those involved in accidents were students, university students, and the elderly.\par \par \uc2 On the other hand, the market share for motor vehicle insurance and general liability insurance remains relatively small. Data from the Indonesian General Insurance Association (AAUI) shows that the market share for motor vehicle insurance dropped from 20.1 percent in 2022 to 18.8 percent in 2023. Similarly, the market share for liability insurance declined from 3.9 percent to 3.8 percent over the same period.\par \par \uc2 Despite this, many are questioning the urgency of mandatory motor vehicle and \uc2 TPL\uc2  insurance. Bhima Yudhistira Adhinegara, Executive Director of the Center of \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Law Studies, stated that without a clear rationale, mandatory \uc2 TPL\uc2  insurance seems like a contrived \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  aimed at extracting \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  funds using various means. \u8220\'20\'1CThis is similar to the previously discussed mandatory Tapera (\b \highlight22\uc2 Public\b0 \highlight\uc2  Housing Savings), so it\u8217\'20\'19s understandable that the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  suspects an effort to collect funds through mandatory insurance for government purposes,\u8221\'20\'1D he said on August 7.\par \par \uc2 Bhima explained that this suspicion is justified, given the existence of OJK \b \highlight22\uc2 Regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  No. 1/2016 on Investment in Securities for Non-Bank Financial Institutions. According to this \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2 , general insurance companies covering property, motor vehicles, and \uc2 TPL\uc2  are required to allocate at least 20 percent of their total investments in government securities.\par \par \uc2 Bhima pointed out that the insurance premiums collected from the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  must be invested in government bonds or securities. \u8220\'20\'1CThis can be read as part of an effort to mitigate the difficulty of securing \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  financing, especially from foreign investors amid global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  turmoil, leading the government to draw on \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  funds,\u8221\'20\'1D he explained.\par \par \uc2 For motor vehicle manufacturers, mandatory \uc2 TPL\uc2  insurance poses a hurdle to achieving sales targets. Anton Jimmi Suwandi, Marketing Director of Toyota Astra Motor, urged the government to consider the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s purchasing power when setting the premium for mandatory insurance. He warned that the automotive industry would be affected if the minimum premium is set too high.\par \par \uc2 Chair of the Association of Indonesian Automotive Manufacturers (Gaikindo), Yohannes Nangoi, also expressed that mandatory insurance is not relevant given the current decline in car sales. From January to June, new car sales reached only 408,012 units, a sharp drop from the 505,985 units sold in the same period in 2023. Yohannes also pointed out that over 70 percent of car sales are made through bank credit or financing institutions, which already include insurance costs.\par \par \uc2 Irvan Rahardjo, an arbiter at the Indonesian Insurance Mediation and Arbitration Agency, argued that instead of creating a new insurance program, the government should optimize the existing vehicle passenger insurance program managed by Jasa Raharja. The traffic accident insurance is regulated by Law No. 34/1964 on the Road Traffic Accident Fund. \u8220\'20\'1CThis existing program should be expanded to include third-party liability coverage,\u8221\'20\'1D he said.\par \par \uc2 According to Irvan, with a program that has been running for decades, Jasa Raharja should have the flexibility to extend its coverage by utilizing its managed funds. Despite the annual increase in accident rates, he added, the premiums collected have far exceeded the claims paid out. This approach would make the premiums more affordable for the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \u8220\'20\'1CIf left to the industry, not all insurance companies have the same financial capability and health,\u8221\'20\'1D he noted.\par \par \uc2 Irvan revealed that if the government insists on making \uc2 TPL\uc2  insurance a standalone program, there might be an ulterior motive to explore the financial market and boost the insurance industry\u8217\'20\'19s penetration, which is currently very low at just 2.67 percent. \u8220\'20\'1CIt should be remembered that mobilizing insurance funds to support development is much cheaper than relying on bank funds sourced from third-party deposits,\u8221\'20\'1D he explained.\par \par \uc2 Ogi Prastomiyono stated that the implementation of the mandatory insurance scheme is pending the issuance of government regulations as a follow-up to the PPSK Law, which will complement the technical rules of the OJK. According to the PPSK Law, the mandatory insurance program must be implemented no later than two years after the law is enacted, meaning by 2025. Ogi emphasized that the premium rates for mandatory \uc2 TPL\uc2  insurance will be calculated based on the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s ability to pay.\par \par \uc2 Bern Dwyanto, Executive Director of the Indonesian General Insurance Association, said that mandatory \uc2 TPL\uc2  insurance could reduce government\u8217\'20\'19s financial burden in providing compensation to traffic accident victims. This \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  has already been implemented in other countries as a required insurance for all drivers. \u8220\'20\'1CWe are preparing the insurance industry players to support \uc2 TPL\uc2  as mandatory insurance and to increase \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  awareness of the importance of protection in light of traffic risks,\u8221\'20\'1D he said on August 7. According to Bern, the technical details of this \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  are still being discussed with the OJK.\par \par \uc2 Rather than being commercial in nature, AAUI Chairperson Budi Herawan suggested that the mandatory \uc2 TPL\uc2  insurance for motor vehicles should be designed as a non-profit initiative to avoid burdening the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 . The AAUI, which consists of 82 companies, is working on proposing a premium rate that would at least cover the compensation for damages that need to be paid out in the event of a claim. \u8220\'20\'1CThe goal is to implement a premium that does not burden the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 ,\u8221\'20\'1D he said.\par \par \uc2 The management scheme, payment methods, and the choice of operator for this insurance are still undecided. One of the options under consideration is the formation of several insurance consortiums.\par \par \uc2 According to Budi, the AAUI has proposed that insurance payments be made simultaneously with vehicle \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  payments and the renewal of vehicle registration certificates to simplify the process. This approach is similar to the mandatory contributions to the road traffic accident fund paid by vehicle owners or passengers when purchasing travel tickets.\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://images-tm.tempo.co/all/2024/08/15/867811/867811_720.jpg"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Click here to view picture}}}\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://images-tm.tempo.co/all/2024/08/15/867812/867812_1200.jpg"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Click here t