\par\par \b \uc2 BI keeps rate unchanged, sees cut only in Q4 despite Fed signal\b0\par\par\uc2 Deni Ghifari, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \uc2 565 \uc2 words\par \uc2 22 August 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 4\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2024 The Jakarta Post \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI)\uc2  has kept its benchmark interest rate unchanged and sees room for a cut opening up only in the fourth quarter, despite signals pointing to faster monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  easing in the United States.\par \par \uc2 Following the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's monthly \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  meeting in Jakarta on Wednesday, BI Governor \uc2 Perry Warjiyo\uc2  affirmed that the BI Rate remainedat its current level of 6.25 percent.\par \par \uc2 "Consistent with our previous statement, room for a BI Rate [cut] will open up in the fourth quarter of 2024", Perry said, thereby suggesting that no change was to be expected in September either, with BI viewing the third quarter as a time for "further strengthening of the rupiah's exchange rate stability".\par \par \uc2 Trading at Rp 15,520 to the US dollar on Wednesday afternoon, the rupiah has strengthened by 4.52 percent against the greenbackcompared to its position exchange value at the end of July, thanks to portfolio inflows.\par \par \uc2 BI noted that most of the August inflows went into government bonds as opposed to those issued by the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 In the first 20 days of August, foreign capital inflows to Indonesian government bonds amounted to Rp 25.17 trillion (US$1.62 billion), followed by BI-issuedbonds (SRBI) with Rp 10.8 trillion and stocks with Rp 6.5 trillion, Perry saidatWednesday's press briefing.\par \par \uc2 This movement was mainly driven byanticipation of an impending reduction in the \uc2 US Federal Reserve\uc2 's benchmark rate, the federal funds rate (FFR). Perry acknowledged that the latest developments suggested the Fed would cut "faster and more than previously estimated".\par \par \uc2 The governor said there was a more than a 75 percent chance of a 25-basis-point (bps) FFR cut in the Fed's \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  meetingscheduled for Sep. 17 and 18.\par \par \uc2 BI is scheduled to hold its next monthly \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  meeting on the same dates and announce its rate decision just hours before the Fed does.\par \par \uc2 Perry noted that \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in global financial markets had subsided but said risks of a global \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown, as well as geopolitical anxiety amid the US election, "have to be heeded".\par \par \uc2 "I see that it's true how the American \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  seems to be at a turning point. US \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth will likely slow down in the second half, as is the case with inflation.[The impression] is getting firmer that it is headed toward the long-term target of 2 percent," said Perry.\par \par \uc2 He added that a second 25 bps FFR cut was on the table for either November or Decemberand that more cuts were likely to follow in the first and second quarter of next year.\par \par \uc2 Considering the US developments on inflation and monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Bank Danamon economist Hosianna Evalita Situmorang told The Jakarta Post on Wednesday that BI's baseline was "conservative" for the purpose of propping up the rupiah.\par \par \uc2 In an analysis released on Wednesday, Hosianna wrote that a stronger currency was "beneficial for the domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 " by virtue of "keeping prices low, supporting industrial expansion and job creation, which in turn aids \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth".\par \par \uc2 She said Indonesia's monetary authority was likely to cut the BI Rate just once in the second half and wait for the Fed's guidanceand that the positive performance in net international investment was to continue throughout the third quarter.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020240821ek8m0000d\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
