\par\par \b \uc2 Businesses fret over political instability amid elections law uproar\b0\par\par\uc2 Aditya Hadi, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \uc2 672 \uc2 words\par \uc2 24 August 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 2\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2024 The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2 Business have urged the government and lawmakers to immediately resolve the backlash surrounding the revision of the Regional Elections Law, stressing that political instability could hurt the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Thousands of protesters, including students, civil organizations and workers, gathered on Thursday outside of the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  complex in Senayan, Central Jakarta, after the House \b \highlight22\uc2 Legislation\b0 \highlight\uc2  Body (Baleg) rushed to revise the 2016 Regional Elections Law.\par \par \uc2 The goal of this move was to walk back a Constitutional Court ruling on Tuesday that revoked a minimum threshold requirement to nominate candidates in the upcoming regional head elections and keep the minimum age limit of 30 for candidates at the time of registration.\par \par \uc2 The revision would pave way for President \uc2 Joko "Jokowi" Widodo\uc2 's youngest son to run for governor of Central Java. Meanwhile, \uc2 Anies Baswedan\uc2 , who ran against president-elect \uc2 Prabowo Subianto\uc2  in the February election, would be unable to run for the influential post of Jakarta governor.\par \par \uc2 Shinta Kamdani, chairwoman of the Indonesian Employers Association (Apindo), said that businesspeople always uphold democratic processes and respect political dynamics in the country.\par \par \uc2 However, she emphasized that the rule of law is crucial to ensuring a favorable investment and business climate for both domestic and foreign investors.\par \par \uc2 "We hoped for a proper and quick resolution [of the issue], so it does not affect the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  conditions," she said on Thursday, as quoted by Kompas.\par \par \uc2 Budiharjo Iduansjah, chairman of the Indonesia Retail and Tenant Association (Hippindo), also said on Thursday that businesses urged all related stakeholders to calm the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  and ease tension, as quoted from Kontan. He said this was to ensure a safe environment for people to shop and travel.\par \par \uc2 Maulana Yusran, secretary-general of the Indonesian Hotel and Restaurant Association (PHRI), expressed hope that the transition of power from Jokowi to Prabowo could occur smoothly, without leading to a large-scale protest.\par \par \uc2 "It is the next administration's homework to put an end on to the tug-of-war over short-term political interests," he said on Thursday, as quoted by Kontan.\par \par \uc2 Bad precedent with risk to business-related laws\par \par \uc2 Hariyadi Sukamdani, PHRI chairman and a member of Apindo's deputy advisory board, said that if lawmakers and the government pressed on to revise the Regional Elections Law, it would create legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in Indonesia.\par \par \uc2 He is concerned that the decision could set a precedent for other government institutions, signaling that 'existing rule could be bent', including laws and regulations related to businesses.\par \par \uc2 "Then everyone would make their own rules [which may contradict the others], leading to chaos," he said on Thursday, as quoted by Kumparan.\par \par \uc2 Danang Girindrawardana, a member of Apindo's board of experts, said that the government and lawmakers have exhibited "declining ethical practices", which could set a negative example for the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 He emphasized the need for regulatory consistency in both the political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  sectors.\par \par \uc2 "The government seems to be ignoring the investment climate and is only focused on maintaining power. It is a dangerous situation. The business sector will respond negatively," he said on Thursday, as quoted by Kompas.\par \par \uc2 He warned that if this prolonged, it could lead to businesses delaying their investments and layoffs, putting pressure on \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth.\par \par \uc2 The impact could also lead to declining purchasing power and thereby declining state revenue, he added.\par \par \uc2 The IDX Composite, the country's stock market benchmark index, fell by 0.87 percent to 7,488 points on Thursday's closing following the protests.\par \par \uc2 It then rebounded 0.74 percent to 7,544 points on Friday's closing after the House announced the cancelation of the Regional Elections Law revision during the day.\par \par \uc2 The rupiah weakened against the greenback throughout Thursday with the exchange rate around Rp 15,700 per United States dollar during intraday trading, from below Rp 15,500 per dollar in the morning.\par \par \uc2 The trend lasted until Friday morning before strengthening to around Rp 15,600 per dollar in the late afternoon.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020240823ek8o0000h\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
