\par\par \b \uc2 Long road ahead for Indonesia's jet fuel industry\b0\par\par\uc2 Divya Karyza, The Jakarta Post, Jakarta \par \uc2 768 \uc2 words\par \uc2 26 August 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 2\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2024 The Jakarta Post \par \par \uc2 The government is inviting private oil and gas companies to produce aviation turbine fuel (avtur) as it seeks to bring down airfares, but experts say Indonesia lacks a competitive advantage in the industry, making it unattractive for investment.\par \par \uc2 Coordinating Maritime Affairs and Investment Minister \uc2 Luhut Pandjaitan\uc2  said Indonesia had to invite aviation fuel producers other than state-owned oil and gas firm \uc2 Pertamina\uc2  to produce cheaper avtur and thereby allow for lower airline ticket prices in the country.\par \par \uc2 However,investment in refineries to process crude oil is costly, not to mention the fact that Indonesia remains reliant on imports of crude oil, Moshe Rizal, who heads the investment committee of the Association of Oil and Gas Companies (Aspermigas) told The Jakarta Post on Thursday.\par \par \uc2 Moreover, oil refineries do not produce avturexclusively, but also make other types of fuel depending on market demand.\par \par \uc2 "No one wants to build a refinery without securing demand, this is a multibillion-dollar investment. Investors must know which airline companies are willing to buy the product first," he said, adding that it "makes more sense" to focus on developing sustainable aviation fuel (SAF) production instead, given Indonesia's position as the world's largest crude palm oil (CPO) producer.\par \par \uc2 After a press conference held on Monday at the Bali International Air Show (BIAS), Luhut said the government was welcoming private companies to invest in aircraft refueling depot (DPPU) projects, especially those located in eastern regions of the country.\par \par \uc2 He went on to say that Indonesia had to leverage its strategic geographical conditions to develop the air transportation sector and accelerate \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, citing the \uc2 International Air Transport Association\uc2 's (\uc2 IATA\uc2 ) projection that Indonesia will become the world's fourth-largest aviation market in 2037.\par \par \uc2 "This is not too long from now, with 390 million passengers, we must develop our aviation industry. We must encourage this great potential," he was quoted as saying by CNBC Indonesia.\par \par \uc2 Citing data from the Transportation Ministry, the \uc2 Business Competition Supervisory Commission (KPPU)\uc2  said on Wednesday that the price of avtur in Indonesiawas 22 percent to 43 percent higher than in other countries because of \uc2 Pertamina\uc2 's monopoly.\par \par \uc2 Deswin Nur, the KPPU's head of \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  relations, said \uc2 Pertamina\uc2 's monopoly had resulted in inefficiency in the formation of avtur prices. Thus, he believed that encouraging the entry of other avtur producers could create competition in pricing, quality, service and after-sales.\par \par \uc2 "So we hope avtur prices can go down because of competition [in the domestic market] and regulatory improvements can be put in place," he said, as reported by Bloomberg Technoz.\par \par \uc2 Certainty for SAF development\par \par \uc2 The government has set its sights on making Southeast Asia's largest \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  one of the world's prominent SAF suppliers, but experts told the Post that the environmental costs and competitiveness in the global aviation industry should be given due consideration.\par \par \uc2 Indonesia has been identified as a potential SAF feedstock supplier and has run pilot projects on the use of biofuel for aviation since 2021.\par \par \uc2 However, to date, Chandra Asri and \uc2 LX International\uc2 's SAF plant announced in 2022 is the only notable SAF project that could potentially become operational before the end of the decade besides \uc2 Pertamina\uc2 's, according to \uc2 Artem Abramov\uc2 , partner and head of clean technology research at \uc2 Rystad Energy\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 "Since the initial announcement, progress has been limited because of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  regarding demand and financial incentives, which suggests that additional government action is needed to ensure that the industry flourishes," he told the Post on Thursday, saying that Indonesia had the potential to become a major SAF market in the long run, considering theaddressable market for jet fuel and its established used cooking oil (UCO) infrastructure.\par \par \uc2 "So, there is considerable opportunity to redirect feedstock to the domestic market if demand increases," he added.\par \par \uc2 The Office of the Coordinating Maritime Affairs and Investment Minister said in a statement issued in May that a presidential \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  on thenational road map for the development of SAF was slated to be introduced onthe sidelines of BIAS in September.\par \par \uc2 In the road map, the government will focus on the utilization of UCO and CPO residue as raw materials for SAF. It will also study the possibility of using seaweed as an alternative SAF raw material.\par \par \uc2 "We are talking about used cooking oil that will be processed, and this has been done in Malaysia and Singapore. We need to think about CPO, and seaweed can be cultivated to become a biofuel. It should be an opportunity," Luhut said in the statement.\par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020240826ek8q00006\par }\page {\par\fs20\uc2 Business\par \b  \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia \highlight\uc2  Projects Rupiah to Range Between Rp 15,300 and Rp 15,700 in 2025\b0\par\par\uc2 325 \uc2 words\par \uc2 27 August 2024\par \uc2 The Jakarta Globe\par \uc2 JGLOBE\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2024. PT Jakarta Globe Media. \par \par \uc2 Jakart